CBRE Capital Markets WA & Australian Healthcare & Social Infrastructure are pleased to offer for sale 2 Clarkshill Road, Secret Harbour –a high-quality healthcare investment strategically located adjacent to a Woolworths/Coles/ALDI shopping centre in the Secret Harbour commercial precinct.

The property is available to purchase individually or in a portfolio along with the Mildura Medical Centre located in regional Victoria. Please request further details of Mildura asset if of interest.

+ Secret Harbour is an established coastal suburb with a captured market for medical, retail and commercial business operators due to strategic location between the Rockingham and Mandurah City Centres.

+ With 9.5 years remaining on the anchor medical tenant lease and 2 x 5 year further options, the subject property is well positioned for a steady income stream over the long term. As a long term operator in Secret Harbour, the medical and pharmacy operators are well placed for continued growth of the business as the region continues to perform positively.

+ The performance of the WA economy through the pandemic has been complimented by further momentum in the states resources and construction sectors into 2021. These macro fundamentals are particularly beneficial to Secret Harbour, with a complimentary mix of FIFO workers and sea-change retiree’s both fueling patronage of the commercial and medical facilities.

+ As we navigate the unique and dynamic marketplace resulting from the Covid-19 Pandemic, healthcare has emerged as one of the stand-out ‘essential services’, making it a priority asset class for investors seeking to strengthen their portfolio with highly defensive income sources.

On behalf of Centuria, CBRE and JLL are pleased to present the opportunity to acquire a 100% freehold interest in a premium healthcare asset, Perth Clinic, located at 21-29 Havelock Street, West Perth WA. 

Comprising some 4,856 sqm of accommodation, the three-level mental health hospital is complimented by an adjacent, recently refurbished office building occupied by specialist doctors and Perth Clinic administration.

The property is wholly leased to Perth Clinic until January 2033 and is Perth’s largest mental healthcare facility, which has operated from the property since 1996.  

The purpose-built hospital and consists of 100 licenced beds with private ensuites, a specialised treatment theatre, commercial-scale kitchen and various administrative and group session rooms. 

Strategically located on Havelock Street in West Perth, opposite Parliament House and only 900m from the Perth CBD, the property occupies a 4,487 sqm corner site making it one of the largest land holdings in the tightly held West Perth market.

The Perth Clinic represents an exceptionally rare opportunity to acquire a long WALE asset in the highly coveted healthcare sector and is the most significant healthcare asset to be offered to market in Perth in recent times.

The property is offered for sale via an Expressions of Interest campaign closing Friday 18th June 2021 at 2pm AWST.
